The paper deals with the detection and prevention of Botnets and Malware in an enterprise network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves monitoring active processes on each node of the network, which suggests a focus on network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of algorithms to detect and combat Bots indicates a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the network algorithm analyzing conversations to and from the hosts of the network, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and information theory (cs.SI).
